BUILD-A-BOOTY is back! And this is the masterclass! 

The masterclass is a take on the sitcom, “The Office” but instead at the gym🤪 cause if an office can look like such an inviting place why does the gym have to feel intimidating? 
The Masterclass promotes the culture of training together- this not only adds a fun element to your daily session but studies suggest it heightens motivation, increases accountability and also improves performance. 

Ashi and I have trained together more times than I can count- and I’m so grateful to be in a position to motivate and help my near and dear. 

So here’s the sign you’re looking for- make your interactions more than just going out and drinking with friends- see them at their best and worst- 

What’ll come out of it? 

Growth- in your relationship and in your practice

Good things come in threes- D3, Omega 3, Magnesium

Took a little inspiration from the @vogueindia what’s in my bag trend- and gave it a hard dose of supplementation! 

Why these work for me- 

1. D3- improves bone health, strengthens immunity, supports muscle function and recovery 

2. Omega 3- it’s an anti-inflammatory, improves protein synthesis and supports brain function 

3. Magnesium- improves sleep quality, aids muscle relaxation, replenishes your ATP stores, supports hormone and gut health. 

But don’t just go by what I’m saying- read up about every supplement you choose to consume- the dosage, benefits, side effects etc 

And remember not to supplement ur way to debt😘

This weekend, I had the honor of attending the Cosmopolitan Blogger Awards 2024 as a nominee for Fitness Influencer of the Year (North)—and to understand why it matters you have to get to know me a little better :) 

Growing up as the “fat kid,” the weight I carried wasn’t just physical. Even after losing it, the fear of scales, calorie counting, and chasing a smaller silhouette consumed me, bringing me at the brink of an eating disorder.

After years of such a complicated relationship with my body I asked myself- what would it take to not treat the place I live in like something I hate. 

That’s when I met movement. 

At first, training was only ever to be “thin” But soon things shifted- my thinking changed- the functionality of my body that I had be nonchalantly ignoring, hit me in the face when I did my first pull up. Suddenly it wasn’t about the size of my body but the incredible things I could do with it. My first few seconds of a handstand- strengthened that belief. And then came along the @cosmoindia blogger awards. 

It was my “look mom, I’m a rich man” moment because the same girl who was once afraid weighing scales and food now stands in front of you as one of the nominees of the “Fitness Influencer of the Year”proud to say she respects every inch of her body.

Kisses to all the people who helped me put this stunning look together-

Emeralds- @amarisjewelsofficial (obviously😘) 
Makeup & Hair- @sdangofficial 

A big thank you to @cosmoindia @lovecolorbar for putting this fabulous night together🩷

How to survive her period cycle- a manual for men

Ovulation phase-😘

Duration- 48 hours 

What happens- estrogen is still up, but so is testosterone🌶️ FSH and LH are released- this is the fertility period 

What she needs- attention and cuddles 

Luteal Phase- lol good luck 

Duration- 5 of the worst days 

What happens- progesterone hikes, cortisol hikes, estrogen dips- welcome to PMS- it sucks 

What she needs- YOUR PATIENCE! Food and emotional support! 

Here’s to wishing she doesn’t smack u in the face this month😘

How to survive her period cycle- a manual for men 

Menstrual Phase- 

Duration- 3-5 days

What happens- estrogen is low, slight hike in cortisol (stress hormone)- increased appetite, irritability and anxiety. 

What she needs- hot water bottle, emotional support, love and patience 

Follicular phase- 

Duration- 10-14 days 

What happens- estrogen on the rise, and so is her mood 

What she needs- compliments, quality time and spontaneity!! 

That’s all we have for today- but do come back for part 2- because the weather is about to get ghastly⚡️

Since Bryan asked- now I gotta tell you what i eat in a day :P 

Calories- 1934 
Macros- P- 117gms | C- 116gms | F- 105 | total sugar- 21gms

Early morning- water + 8 almonds + coconut milk matcha 

Breakfast- 2 full eggs + avocado (50gm) + feta + a crispy slice of sourdough 

Lunch- lamb (150gms) + sweet potato (70gm) + broccoli (70gms) 

Snack- 2 dark chocolate pieces + 4 walnuts + 1tbsp nut butter 

Dinner- chicken tikka (150gms) + quinoa (100gms) + broccoli (70gms)

Late night- hot chocolate @minus.30 + pistachios

Do you need the same macros i need? No! But do you need to make an active effort to make sure you fuel your body the right way? I think you know the answer

Here’s your guide to make your matcha less pretentious and more edible😌

I switched to matcha soon after my coffee addiction turned into plain anxiety. I still needed something to keep me going through the day and I won’t lie matcha just looked too pretty not to try! 

It did take a little getting used to but the difference was apparent- first few things I noticed- 

1. 0 jitters 
2. I was less acidic 
3. Didn’t feel dehydrated 
4. No energy crash (wouldn’t need one for a couple hours after) 

See it’s so much more than pretty🤌🏻

I like mine as an iced latte- and while it may take some time to become palatable for you it’s definitely worth a shot!
